column3: @MarcoFalke Yes, it is not critical. In fact, just removing the unused declaration in main.h (unused because it's a different function from the one defined in .cpp, even if the name it's the same, that's why the mistake didn't break anything) would also solve it. Which makes me think...should I also make the function static (the change would be +3 -5 instead of +5 -5)?\n
As the compiler doesn't catch this error, the declaration is clearly unnecessary and should be removed IMO\n
Made static and renamed PR and commit (more documentation in the commit itself).\n
